  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Central Dairy Scale Up Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is designed to enhance efficiency, productivity and proficiency of the dairy industry, resulting in income increase and employment benefits for small holder producers and increased access to safe nutritional dairy products for low income consumers. The project will identify and promote productive strategies and techniques in livestock production that increase returns in a sustainable way. The project&apos;s goal is to contribute to improving the Malawi dairy sector productivity, efficiency and sustainability. Interventions will be done throughout the value chain, bringing together value chain stakeholders including producers, processors, transporters, regulators, financial service providers and extension workers to enhance their relationships in order to address value chain constraints. Capacity building of business service providers will be conducted as well to enhance the quality of services provided to the producers. Through Heifer International&apos;s successful Dairy Business Hub model, the project will intervene to increase competitiveness of the dairy sector, increase marketing of milk meeting quality standards by producer owned milk bulking businesses, link farmers to business development services and improve consumption of milk and related products particularly in the rural areas. The project will be implemented in three districts namely Dowa, Lilongwe and Mchinji, with existing dairy related activities and high potential for scale up of the sector in the Central region of Malawi. The project is expected to directly benefit 5,000 households (25,000 individuals, 70 percent of targeted households will be women).</narrative>
  </description>
